channel.title: SCAR Source Code?
channel.description:
Well, I am basicly asking if anyone has or knows where to get the SCAR source code. I've been looking for quite sometime. I do not plan to publish this for anything related to RS2 or anything that would compete against Freddy1990.com. I am looking for this to possibly crack a RSC private server's detection.
If you know or have the SCAR source code, then please.. Leave a post or message me.
Thanks in advance.

item.title: SCAR Source Code?
item.dc:creator: @WT-Fakawi WT-Fakawi
item.description:
@WT-Fakawi wrote:

You could also start using Simba.

[i]
Simba is the ultimate Macro Engine.

* Simba is free to the bone; you don't have to pay anything for it and you can discover exactly how it works. [b]It is open source.[/b]
* Cross platform. Simba 0.91 is only for Windows, but there are already versions of Simba on Linux, and Mac support is hopefully following.
* Actively developed; it is still under heavily development; so don't be amazed when you see regular updates that touch core features of Simba (the GUI).
* Open minded. We welcome all sorts of criticism and ideas.
* Documented. There is documentation on how to use Simba as well on how Simba actually works.
* Extensible; you can write your own extensions (or plug-ins, depending on how you want to call them) for Simba. You don't need anything but Simba to do this; and the extensions can vary from updaters, little user interface enhancements, to powerful tools like DTM editors.
* Simba is stable and quite fast
* Upcoming support for other programming languages.

Simba features:

* Run multiple scripts
* Code hints and completion
* Colour Picker History
* Auto updates
* Handful of useful tools to aid you while scripting.
* Full access to all settings

… and much, much more.[/i]
